AB  - This paper uses characteristics analysis to explain the demand for Swiss banknotes by denomination. We find that the characteristics of banknotes explain to a large extent the currency mix that the public wishes to hold. An increase in the price level and in real income is found to favor large denominations, while an increase in velocity and in interest rates is found to increase the share of small bills. The model is used to predict the demand for a Frs. 200 banknote, a denomination which does not exist at the moment in Switzerland.
